  "prompt": "What symptoms of Post Traumatic Stress Disorder does Katniss suffer from in The Hunger Games: Catching Fire (2013 movie)?",
  "response": "In \"Catching Fire,\" Katniss exhibits several symptoms of Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) following her experiences in the 74th Hunger Games:\n\n1. Hypervigilance - She is constantly on alert and easily startled, especially by sudden movements or loud noises\n\n2. Nightmares - She frequently experiences disturbing dreams related to her traumatic experiences in the arena\n\n3. Emotional numbness - Katniss struggles to connect emotionally with others and appears detached at times\n\n4. Flashbacks - She has intrusive memories of violent scenes from the previous Hunger Games, which can be triggered by specific stimuli\n\n5. Survivor's guilt - She feels responsible for the deaths of other tributes and is haunted by the memories of those she couldn't save\n\nThese symptoms are depicted throughout the film as Katniss continues to process the psychological impact of her violent experiences in the first Hunger Games.",
